1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,140
AI will not fix a bad ICP.

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:03,870
It will just help you reach the wrong

3
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:04,680
accounts faster.

4
00:00:05,180 --> 00:00:07,150
Ideal customer profile is a strategic

5
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,700
decision, not a data problem.

6
00:00:08,970 --> 00:00:11,050
It requires the leadership team to

7
00:00:11,170 --> 00:00:12,240
answer hard questions.

8
00:00:12,590 --> 00:00:15,050
Which customers actually get value from

9
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:15,730
what we sell?

10
00:00:16,060 --> 00:00:17,880
Which ones renew, expand, and refer?

11
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:19,970
Which ones churn, complain, and drain

12
00:00:20,030 --> 00:00:20,390
the team?

13
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:22,810
AI can help you analyze patterns in your

14
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:24,120
customer base once you have enough

15
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:24,500
signal.

16
00:00:25,060 --> 00:00:27,080
It can surface firmographic clusters,

17
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:28,920
usage patterns, and expansion

18
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:29,500
indicators.

19
00:00:30,220 --> 00:00:32,250
But it cannot make the strategic call

20
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,800
about which market to focus on.

21
00:00:33,990 --> 00:00:35,220
That is a human decision.

22
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:38,040
The teams that use AI most effectively

23
00:00:38,090 --> 00:00:39,800
in their go-to-market motion have

24
00:00:39,860 --> 00:00:41,600
already done the hard work of defining

25
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:43,660
who they are actually built to serve.

26
00:00:44,060 --> 00:00:45,940
AI then helps them find more of those

27
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:48,140
buyers and reach them with a relevant

28
00:00:48,190 --> 00:00:48,910
reason to talk.

29
00:00:49,460 --> 00:00:52,090
Follow A-Gent for the agent-first GTM

30
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:52,550
playbook.
